					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13602166#post-4735041</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13602166/scp-5818#post-4735041</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 31 Jul 2020 17:24:02 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Tao McCawley</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3212944</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I liked this.</p> <p>First off, your writing prose is really good. The Shakespearean lines are top notch.</p> <p>Now I want a burger.</p> <p>Either way, I feel the meat of this proverbial burger comes from the transcript. At the same time, and this may sound a bit reductionist, it feels like it needs more to it than &quot;It's a burger that goes Shakespearean and kills it's cook when created by inciting a mob.&quot; I feel like there's more that can be added to this, either via another addendum, or something similar.</p> <p>I guess what I'm trying to say is this burger could use more meat.</p> <p>Either way, I love it. Plus vote from me.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
